.085171]},{"section":20,"text":"It's the most common genetic cause of intellectual disability and is associated with a range of physical features that match the findings here.","dimension":17,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046928,0.068986,0.07932,0.087425,0.08773,0.088692,0.092352,0.093266,0.091628,0.090978,0.087289,0.085406],"unified_progress":[0.035771,0.058287,0.072888,0.082502,0.088404,0.094934,0.095961,0.098642,0.098155,0.097299,0.092507,0.08465]},{"section":21,"text":"I don't see any other condition that presents with such a combination of features.","dimension":6,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039915,0.066666,0.079581,0.086249,0.089728,0.09099,0.091747,0.092492,0.091513,0.096828,0.089774,0.084517],"unified_progress":[0.035274,0.062351,0.074832,0.086127,0.090399,0.093019,0.095942,0.097312,0.097375,0.098694,0.090253,0.078422]},{"section":22,"text":"For example, other syndromes like Turner syndrome or Klinefelter's have different presentations.","dimension":15,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030332,0.053114,0.069395,0.080276,0.092917,0.099218,0.1083,0.11015,0.10512,0.09857,0.083605,0.069005],"unified_progress":[0.02968,0.057132,0.078505,0.090794,0.098367,0.11003,0.10587,0.10384,0.098977,0.093254,0.075746,0.057803]},{"section":23,"text":"So, the most likely diagnosis is Down syndrome.","dimension":8,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.022712,0.04081,0.052607,0.05938,0.067606,0.073231,0.077587,0.08538,0.090511,0.12104,0.13469,0.17444],"unified_progress":[0.021727,0.041416,0.052031,0.063894,0.068483,0.07929,0.081151,0.091608,0.09675,0.10555,0.13289,0.16521]},{"section":24,"text":"The infant exhibits multiple physical features consistent with Down syndrome, including hypotonia, poor Moro reflex, upslanting palpebral fissures, epicanthal folds, excess nuchal skin, an enlarged tongue, clinodactyly, and a single transverse palmar crease.","dimension":14,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_